# Subprocesses — Bun.spawn only

Applies to all TypeScript under **`apps/`** and **`packages/`**.

## Required

Use **`Bun.spawn`** with an **argv array** (no shell) when invoking
external programs (`forge`, `cast`, `doppler`, etc.).

Read exit status from **`await proc.exited`**. Capture or inherit
stdio via spawn options (`stdin`, `stdout`, `stderr`: `"pipe"`,
`"inherit"`, `"ignore"`, or a `Blob`/`Buffer` for one-shot stdin).

Full patterns: [docs/agents/subprocess.md](../../docs/agents/subprocess.md).

## Forbidden

- `node:child_process` (`spawn`, `exec`, `execFile`, `execSync`,
  `spawnSync`, `fork`)
- `import … from "child_process"`
- Bun’s **`$` shell template** for subprocesses (use `Bun.spawn`
  instead for explicit argv and consistent error handling)

Shared helpers belong in `packages/` when two or more tools need the
same spawn wrapper.
